The device has one coaxial connector which handles both WAN (incoming Cable) :and LAN (MoCA 2.0 via an ''Entropic Communications'' EN2710-LS2 IC).
The FCC internal photos show a ''SiTel'' <!--(now acquired by ''Dialog Semiconductor'')--> SC14441 DECT 6.0 chip. :The datasheet (FCC and non) describes the DECT functionality as optional. This device will likely be used with ''{{Approved by service|Comcast}}'''s Xfinity service {{see also|Technicolor TC8717C|Foxconn}} {{lowercase}}
